## Project Structure
```
packages/
  untaped-core/     # Shared utilities (YAML loader, template renderer, error formatting)
  untaped-ansible/  # Domain logic for Tower resources (models, API wrappers, CLI sub-app)
  untaped-cli/      # Entrypoint that registers sub-apps with Typer
tests/
  contract/       # API contract tests
  integration/    # End-to-end workflow tests
  unit/          # Individual component tests
specs/
  001-mvp-scope-resources/  # Current feature specifications and design
```

## Constitution
- The constitution is the source of truth for the project.
- You must follow the constitution at all times.
- It is located at `.specify/memory/constitution.md`.


## Commands
# MVP CLI commands (create, update, delete) for job templates and workflow job templates
# All commands support --config-file, --vars-file, --var, --dry-run, --verbose flags
# Validation-first processing: Load YAML → Render Jinja2 → Validate Pydantic → Apply to Tower API

## Code Style
Python: Follow constitutional principles - config-driven architecture, validation-first processing, modular UV workspaces, thin CLI design
Testing: TDD mandatory - tests first, then implementation to make them pass
Error handling: Field-specific validation errors with actionable suggestions

